      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T19:54:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Overall I think this design doc needs to be made more specific as to what use cases it\u0027s trying to implement, and tie those out with what Redfish supports.  If someone wants to configure a firewall generically, there are lots of APIs for doing that directly and in my opinion OpenBMC doesn\u0027t need to invent a new one.  If there\u0027s use cases specific to the BMC that we want to support, we might model some of those directly and specifically, but that\u0027s not what this doc does.\n\nThis is roughly the same as why we don\u0027t model a generic \"gpio\" on dbus.  We\u0027re trying to model portable and movable use cases, not just taking one API and splatting it to another.",
      "revId": "e8e6b143abe6d3e5ee82f0b4952b532558537aa0",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
